snippet: Weak reports on confidence and factory output, combined with fears that the Federal Reserve could end its stimulus program, weighed on investors.
abstract: Disappointing reports about economy, consumer confidence and factory output, combined with fears that Federal Reserve could end its stimulus program, weighs on investors, pushing stock market lower.
lead_paragraph: Weak reports on confidence and factory output, combined with fears that the Federal Reserve could end its stimulus program, weighed on investors.

headline.main: Shares End the Week Down After 2 Dissatisfying Reports
